At least 17 people sustained injuries when a taxi overturned on the N2 South-bound highway in Galleria, KwaZulu-Natal on Monday.On arrival, paramedics found the taxi lying on its roof in the centre medium. Passengers had already climbed out of the vehicle and were found scattered around the scene.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said Paramedics inspected the patients and found a total of 17 people had been injured. And their injuries ranged from minor to serious .All patients were treated on the scene and once treated, they were transported to various hospitals in the area for further treatment.The details surrounding this incident are not yet known.-TNA Reporter 